        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://newyork.craigslist.org/brk/ret/6040685859.html"></div>
        </div>
<a href="http://www.solarreviews.com/solar-companies/top-100-residential-solar-power-contractors-2016/" rel="nofollow">Level Solar</a> is one of the top rated solar companies in the Nation. We help families save money on their energy bills by installing solar panels on their home at <b>no-cost</b> allowing them to power their home with energy that is local, renewable and less expensive. In short, we help local families save money while making a positive impact for our planet and our future.
<p><b>Level Solar is currently growing our Staten Island office</b> and are looking for a few talented, passionate individuals to join our team. If you want to begin or advance your career and be a part of building a great company while helping families reduce their energy costs, and building a more sustainable future <b>we want to meet you.</b>
<p><b>The Position</b><ul>
As an Ambassador for Level Solar, you will use your sales and/or outreach skills in neighborhoods in and around Staten Island. You will educate homeowners about the benefits of transitioning to solar energy, and set appointments for our Solar Consultants who will explain how Level Solar can help them save money. Level Solar is a rapidly growing team, and there are opportunities to take on more responsibility and advance quickly. 
</ul>
<p><b>Qualifications:</b><ul>
<li>Excellent communication skills and a passion for clean energy
<li>Ability to interact with a diverse customer base while delivering consistently excellent customer service
<li>Relentless optimism, infectious energy and positive attitude
<li>A strong commitment to our core values of quality, unity, integrity, positivity, safety, agility and responsibility
<li>A college degree strongly preferred but we also value candidates with relevant work experience and those currently pursuing their education
<li>Must have a valid driver's license and access to reliable transportation
<li>Ability to pass a DMV and background check and drug test
<li>Must be 18 or over
</ul>
<p><b>We Offer:</b><ul>
<li>Paid Training with leading industry experts; You will become an expert in solar energy
<li>Personal and professional development
<li>Base salary + Commission and bonuses
<li>A fun, positive team!
</ul>
<p><b>Earn $700-$850/week or more with base pay and commission. Paid training with industry experts and benefits.</b>
<p><b>TO APPLY: Reply to this post with your resume.</b>
<p><b>Level Solar is an equal opportunity employer </b> and does not discriminate against any employee or applicant on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. We promote a culture of inclusion and respect.</p></p></p></li></li></li></li></p></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></p></p></p>    </section>

